    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't even want a \"next chapter.\" that's the thing. a book doesn't keep adding pages once the story has actually ended. it just becomes filler. it becomes a way to waste paper. it feels like my story reached its natural conclusion, and now i'm just... lingering. like a ghost in a house that's already been emptied out. doesn't it ever feel like some things are just meant to be finished?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
